article.description: Utah Valley St. 98, Haskell Indian Nations 50
article.headline: Utah Valley St. 98, Haskell Indian Nations 50
article.linkText: Utah Valley St. 98, Haskell Indian Nations 50
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Isiah Williams scored 20 points to lead five Utah Valley players in double figures as the Wolverines routed Haskell 98-50 on Tuesday night. Geddes Robinson had 15 points and 14 rebounds, and Ben Aird had 14 points and 12 rebounds for Utah Valley (7-8). Jordan Swarbrick had 17 points and Shawn Deadwiler 10 for the Wolverines, who never trailed, outrebounded Haskell 50-21 and led by up to 54 points. Marcellous Hill led Haskell with 22 points. John Garrick added 10 points and a team-high six rebounds. Haskell, an NAIA school, played the game as an exhibition.
